    16→<div class="mdbook-version">
    17→Version: {{ mdbook-version }}
    18→</div>
    19→
    20→**mdBook** is a command line tool to create books with Markdown.
    21→It is ideal for creating product or API documentation, tutorials, course materials or anything that requires a clean,
    22→easily navigable and customizable presentation.
    23→
    24→* Lightweight [Markdown] syntax helps you focus more on your content
    25→* Integrated [search] support
    26→* Color [syntax highlighting] for code blocks for many different languages
    27→* [Theme] files allow customizing the formatting of the output
    28→* [Preprocessors] can provide extensions for custom syntax and modifying content
    29→* [Backends] can render the output to multiple formats
    30→* Written in [Rust] for speed, safety, and simplicity
    31→* Automated testing of [Rust code samples]
    32→
    33→This guide is an example of what mdBook produces.
    34→mdBook is used by the Rust programming language project, and [The Rust Programming Language][trpl] book is another fine example of mdBook in action.
    35→
    36→[Markdown]: format/markdown.md
    37→[search]: guide/reading.md#search
    38→[syntax highlighting]: format/theme/syntax-highlighting.md
    39→[theme]: format/theme/index.html
    40→[preprocessors]: format/configuration/preprocessors.md
    41→[backends]: format/configuration/renderers.md
    42→[Rust]: https://www.rust-lang.org/
    43→[trpl]: https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/
    44→[Rust code samples]: cli/test.md
    45→
    46→## Contributing
    47→
    48→mdBook is free and open source. You can find the source code on
    49→[GitHub](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook) and issues and feature requests can be posted on
    50→the [GitHub issue tracker](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/issues). mdBook relies on the community to fix bugs and
    51→add features: if you'd like to contribute, please read
    52→the [CONTRIBUTING](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md) guide and consider opening
    53→a [pull request](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/pulls).
    54→
    55→## License
    56→
