    17→## The build process
    18→
    19→The process of rendering a book project goes through several steps.
    20→
    21→1. Load the book
    22→    - Parse the `book.toml`, falling back to the default `Config` if it doesn't
    23→       exist
      →…
    30→## Using `mdbook` as a library
    31→
    32→The `mdbook` binary is just a wrapper around the underlying mdBook crates,
    33→exposing their functionality as a command-line program. If you want to
    34→programmatically drive mdBook, you can use the [`mdbook-driver`] crate.
    35→This can be used to add your own functionality or tweak the build process.
    36→
