format/theme/index-hbs.md
     1→# index.hbs
     2→
     3→`index.hbs` is the handlebars template that is used to render the book. The
     4→markdown files are processed to html and then injected in that template.
     5→
     6→If you want to change the layout or style of your book, chances are that you
     7→will have to modify this template a little bit. Here is what you need to know.
     8→
     9→## Data
    10→
    11→A lot of data is exposed to the handlebars template with the "context". In the
    12→handlebars template you can access this information by using
    13→
    14→```handlebars
    15→{{name_of_property}}
    16→```
    17→
      →…
    41→## Handlebars helpers
    42→
    43→In addition to the properties you can access, there are some handlebars helpers
    44→at your disposal.
    45→
    46→### toc
    47→
    48→The toc helper is used like this
    49→
    50→```handlebars
    51→{{#toc}}{{/toc}}
    52→```
    53→
    54→and outputs something that looks like this, depending on the structure of your
      →…
    80→### resource
    81→
    82→The path to a static file.
    83→It implicitly includes `path_to_root`,
    84→and accounts for files that are renamed with a hash in their filename.
    85→
    86→```handlebars
    87→<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ resource "css/chrome.css" }}">
    88→```
      →…
    90→### fa
    91→
    92→mdBook includes a copy of [Font Awesome Free's](https://fontawesome.com)
    93→MIT-licensed SVG files. It accepts three positional arguments:
    94→
    95→1. Type: one of "solid", "regular", and "brands" (light and duotone are not
    96→   currently supported)
    97→2. Icon: anything chosen from the
    98→   [free icon set](https://fontawesome.com/v6/search)
      →…
